<p class="p">The methodology used to determine the fungal decay was reported elsewhere [
 <xref rid="B52-biomolecules-08-00155" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">52</xref>] and is briefly described here. The severity of fruit decay was evaluated visually according to the following scale: 1 = not damaged, 2 = light damage (&lt;25%), 3 = moderate damage (&gt;25% and &lt;50%), 4 = severe damage (&gt;50 and &lt;75%), and 5 = completely damaged (75–100%) [
 <xref rid="B53-biomolecules-08-00155" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">53</xref>]. The decay index was calculated using the following formula [
 <xref rid="B54-biomolecules-08-00155" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">54</xref>]:
